// Given two integer arrays nums1 and nums2, return an array of their intersection. Each element in the result must be unique and you may return the result in any order.

 HashSet : A HashSet is a class in Java used to store unique elements. So intercetion of two arrays also have common unique elements , that's why we use HashSet . 
 // Main features of HashSet is :
  If you add duplicaate values , it will add only one copy.

  //Time Complexity: O(n+m)
 
 

It belongs to the Java Collections Framework.

// code

class Solution {
    public int[] intersection(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>(); // create a HashSet named set
        HashSet<Integer> ans = new HashSet<>(); // and create another named ans

        // Store nums1 elements in set
        for (int x : nums1) {
            set.add(x); // adds elements to the HashSet
        }

        // Check common elements
        for (int x : nums2) {
            if (set.contains(x)) {
                ans.add(x); // if element is common store it in ans
            }
        }

        // Convert HashSet to array
        int[] result = new int[ans.size()]; // Creates integer array of size equal to answer set size.
        int i = 0;

        for (int x : ans) { // Loop through all elements in ans.
            result[i++] = x;
        }

        return result;


        
    }
}
